---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Resources" description="Free sheet music, recorder organizations, teachers, and other resources for recorder players.">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 md:py-16">
    <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl font-bold text-primary-900 mb-2">Resources</h1>
    <div class="h-px w-24 bg-gold-400 mb-10"></div>

    <!-- Free Sheet Music -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-900 mb-4">Free Sheet Music</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        A wealth of recorder music is available for free online. Here are some of the best sources:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-4">
        <li>
          <a href="https://imslp.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">IMSLP (International Music Score Library Project)</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">The largest collection of free public domain sheet music. Search for recorder sonatas, consort music, and more.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.cpdl.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">CPDL (Choral Public Domain Library)</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Excellent source for vocal music that works well on recorders — Renaissance part-songs, madrigals, and motets.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.8notes.com/recorder/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">8notes — Recorder</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Free sheet music arranged for recorder at various levels, with play-along audio.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.free-scores.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">Free-scores.com</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Large library of free scores including recorder-specific arrangements.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.serpentpublications.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">Serpent Publications</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Free recorder ensemble music, including many pieces suitable for chapter meetings.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Recorder Organizations -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-900 mb-4">Recorder Organizations</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4">
        <li>
          <a href="https://americanrecorder.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">American Recorder Society (ARS)</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Our parent organization. Membership includes <em>American Recorder</em> magazine and access to workshops and events.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.chathambaroque.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">Chatham Baroque / Renaissance &amp; Baroque</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Pittsburgh's early music ensemble, presenting concerts of Medieval, Renaissance, Baroque, and Classical music.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Workshops -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-900 mb-4">Workshops &amp; Summer Programs</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4">
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.earlymusicweekmideast.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">Mideast Early Music Workshop</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Held every July at LaRoche University right here in Pittsburgh. Primarily recorder, with classes in viol, baroque flute, voice, early brass, and crumhorn. Many PRS members attend — a favorite summer program.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.amherstearlymusic.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">Amherst Early Music</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Workshops and online classes throughout the year, including the Spring Break Workshop in April.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Finding a Teacher -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-900 mb-4">Finding a Teacher</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        If you're looking for private recorder instruction, these resources can help:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-4">
        <li>
          <a href="https://americanrecorder.org/find_recorder_teachers.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">ARS Teacher Directory</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Search for recorder teachers by location, including those who offer online lessons.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-primary-600 text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">
        You can also ask at our meetings — members may know of local teachers or be willing to offer guidance.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Recorder Shops -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-900 mb-4">Recorder Shops</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Online retailers specializing in recorders:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-4">
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.vonhuene.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">Von Huene Workshop</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Maker and retailer of fine recorders, based in the Boston area.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.sweetpipes.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">Sweet Pipes</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Recorders, music, and educational materials.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.lazarsearlymusic.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-500 font-semibold underline decoration-teal-300 underline-offset-2">Lazar's Early Music</a>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary-600 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Wide selection of recorders and early music instruments.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Musical Tidbits -->
    <div>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-900 mb-4">Musical Tidbits</h2>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 border border-primary-200 space-y-4 text-primary-700 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          <strong>Did you know?</strong> The recorder is one of the most important wind
          instruments of the Renaissance and Baroque periods. Composers like Handel, Vivaldi,
          Telemann, and Bach all wrote extensively for the instrument.
        </p>
        <p>
          The recorder family spans a huge range — from the tiny garklein (about 6 inches)
          to the sub-contrabass (over 6 feet tall). The most common sizes used in ensemble
          playing are soprano, alto, tenor, and bass.
        </p>
        <p>
          Henry VIII, who composed the song "Pastime with Good Company" (our motto!), was
          known to own a collection of 76 recorders.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
